courses.course_syllabus:
1) Lectures: Introduction of leadership and teamwork
2) Workshops and outdoor activities: Trust-building and Commitment-building
3) Team projects and presentations with guidance with College supervisors:
a) Identify the team goals, the duties and responsibilities of each team member;
b) Team meetings;
c) Accomplishing the team goal;
d) Evaluation and report; and
e) Sharing the experience to other teams.

courses.learning_outcomes:
By the end of the course, students should be able to
1. Describe the development and the nature of manner and etiquette systems;
2. Identify the difference of manner among countries or cultures with the theoretical framework of interpersonal and intercultural communications as well as socialization;
3. Apply the theories and skills to their daily life;
4. Communicate and interact effectively with others;
